gomodel:SYNGO_1599  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors found that Cdh1 is concentrated in the detergent-resistant post-synaptic fractions of adult rat brain, which suggests that there is a tight association between APC and postsynaptic proteins (Fig. 5d).\n\n28/8/2017 Pim\n- Functional data shows that APC/Cdh1 mediates ubituitination of AMPARs, and \"Reduction of synaptic strength by ephrin-A1 or chronic treatment of bicuculline depends on APCCdh1-dependent proteasome degradation pathway\" This is functional evidendce that Cdh1 is indeed localizated in the postsynapse.. Experimental description: Cortical rat neurons" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" ;
        dc:date           "2017-09-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1599" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

